<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11562&amp;p=132919#p132919"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">mikaelmoizt wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />This method of transferring OAM data is not my strong side. It looks pretty hard to do aswell. Consider using $4014 instead.<br /></div><br /><br />There's an additional problem here that most of OAM has not been initialized, so on startup you might have random sprites scattered about. Probably this won't show up on emulators, but it will happen on an NES. The $4014 DMA is really the only effective way to set up sprites. Doing something with just $2004 that works properly outside of an emulator is very tricky. Stick with $4014, and only use it during vblank.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5165">rainwarrior</a> — Fri Aug 22, 2014 6:38 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
